She's about this tall.

66
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:31,611
Hair this long.

67
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,488
Her figure is a bit like mine.

68
00:10:37,400 --> 00:10:39,004
Hands like yours.

69
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:44,691
What are her interests?

70
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,888
Sport clubs? A music group?

71
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:55,244
She rides occasionally.

72
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:58,884
Did you call the stables?
- Yes. Of course.

73
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,561
A diary?

74
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,369
They write online.

75
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,484
Blogs and so on.

76
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:16,723
Did you check the computer?

77
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:19,363
I don't have the passwords.

78
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,482
Thanks.

79
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:55,042
You've been so weird recently.

80
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,480
Really?
- Well...

81
00:11:56,920 --> 00:11:59,241
Is something up at work?
- No.

82
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:03,366
Or is it because Sylvia called again?

83
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:06,849
She didn't call again.
- She'd called about a friend.

84
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:08,724
That got cleared up.

85
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:11,168
You said she didn't call again.

86
00:12:11,400 --> 00:12:14,006
She didn't.
She sent a text message.

87
00:12:16,400 --> 00:12:18,289
There is no friend, right?

88
00:12:21,200 --> 00:12:22,725
Tell me what's up.

89
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:29,805
I have a daughter.

90
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,691
With Sylvia.

91
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,001
What?

92
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,361
She's thirteen.

93
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:39,402
I wanted to put it all behind me.

94
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:41,688
To finish with it. For us, too.

95
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,485
For us?

96
00:12:48,760 --> 00:12:50,125
Yes. I...

97
00:12:53,920 --> 00:12:55,524
I wanted to start over.

98
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:04,891
Why...

99
00:13:06,120 --> 00:13:07,451
Why what?

100
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:12,809
Didn't you ask yourself

101
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:16,884
if I'd have been glad
about this daughter?

102
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,121
Vera,

103
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:21,004
you don't know Sylvia.

104
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,922
Why are you telling me this now?

105
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:39,729
Because she's vanished.

106
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:57,731
Julia!
Do you have a moment?

107
00:14:05,440 --> 00:14:07,761
This is Mr Meinert, Martha's father.

108
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,086
Hello.

109
00:14:10,440 --> 00:14:11,726
You...

110
00:14:11,960 --> 00:14:13,724
are a friend of Martha's?

111
00:14:17,840 --> 00:14:19,410
I'll leave you alone.

112
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:22,285
If you need me,
I'll be in the staff room.

113
00:14:22,760 --> 00:14:24,250
Thanks.

114
00:14:29,560 --> 00:14:32,723
Did Martha give any hint
of where she's gone to?

115
00:14:33,480 --> 00:14:34,811
No.

116
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:40,405
Do you have any idea

117
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,731
where she might be?

118
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:45,771
Nope.

119
00:14:47,440 --> 00:14:49,886
It'd be a relief to us
to know she's well.

120
00:14:50,080 --> 00:14:52,128
If she went away voluntarily.

121
00:14:55,400 --> 00:14:57,164
We want nothing from her.

122
00:14:58,000 --> 00:14:59,240
You understand?

123
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:00,771
Who is "we"?

124
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:02,481
Her mother and I.

125
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:05,490
I thought
you didn't talk to each other.

126
00:15:06,160 --> 00:15:07,446
We do, now.

127
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:09,728
Now that Martha's gone?
- Yes.

128
00:15:15,480 --> 00:15:16,811
Was that it?

129
00:15:18,600 --> 00:15:19,931
Yes.

130
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:21,851
Thanks.

131
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,085
Well?

132
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:41,041
Did you know a schoolmate of Martha's
is missing, too?

133
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:44,163
A boy from an asocial family.

134
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,291
The parents said nothing

135
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:49,131
till the school asked
where the boy is.

136
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:51,204
So that's fine, then?

137
00:15:54,480 --> 00:15:56,482
And did you speak to that Julia?

138
00:15:56,680 --> 00:15:59,650
Yes, of course.
- And did you find it normal?

139
00:15:59,960 --> 00:16:01,564
What do you mean, normal?

140
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:05,043
She doesn't give a shit
that her best friend disappeared.

141
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,208
And how would you know that?

142
00:16:09,480 --> 00:16:11,369
It leaves her cold as ice.

143
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,248
I took this one for the poster.

144
00:16:24,440 --> 00:16:25,851
Did you see it?

145
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:33,328
There aren't many recent ones.
She's camera-shy.

146
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:37,967
Here. Bornholm.

147
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:43,891
She was so small.

148
00:16:49,280 --> 00:16:51,442
If I'd taken more care of her...

149
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:57,611
You couldn't have followed her around.

150
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,608
She wouldn't have just left.

151
00:17:07,960 --> 00:17:10,201
She would have said something.

152
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:19,121
Maybe she's long dead now.

153
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:33,486
You think it's normal
that children just vanish?

154
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:36,081
It's not as unusual
as you might think.

155
00:18:36,280 --> 00:18:37,327
Oh, no?

156
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:39,602
90 percent of all missing people
are teenagers.

157
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:42,929
80 percent of them turn up in the end.

158
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:46,561
What about the other 20 percent?

159
00:18:47,560 --> 00:18:49,528
I understand your concerns.

160
00:18:49,720 --> 00:18:51,051
I'm a father myself.

161
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,969
You have my telephone number.

162
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:58,207
Good bye.
- Good bye.

163
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:01,688
2005 friends!
How can that be?

164
00:19:02,760 --> 00:19:04,603
She doesn't know them all.

165
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:09,042
What does it mean, Martha
is a member of the?ying rats group"?

166
00:19:09,240 --> 00:19:10,810
That she's a member.

167
00:19:11,560 --> 00:19:13,528
Can you click for more info?

168
00:19:14,400 --> 00:19:16,084
There's nothing going on.

169
00:19:17,200 --> 00:19:18,725
What does the rat mean?

170
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:21,369
Nothing. it's just a logo.

171
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,370
What kind of group is it?

172
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:27,322
We make dates and have parties.

173
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:29,845
What kind of parties?

174
00:19:30,600 --> 00:19:32,682
We post bottles of beer.

175
00:19:33,960 --> 00:19:35,689
Not real beer, of course.

176
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:48,523
You realise Martha's vanished,
that she might be dead?

177
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:51,291
You're the one asking the questions.

178
00:19:58,200 --> 00:20:01,522
MISSING
MARTHA MEINERT

179
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:21,811
Hello?
- My name is Meinert, I...

180
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,480
I'm the father of a girl
at your son's school.

181
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:25,886
I'd like to talk to you.

182
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:29,243
My daughter recently vanished...
- Don't bother me.

183
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,805
Hello?

184
00:21:18,840 --> 00:21:20,285
Yes?

185
00:21:20,520 --> 00:21:23,364
My name's Meinert,
I'd like to talk to you.

186
00:21:25,560 --> 00:21:27,289
My daughter has also vanished.

187
00:21:27,480 --> 00:21:30,086
Like your son.
I share your troubles.

188
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:37,484
I only want to talk to you!

189
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,804
Do you have news from your son?
Anything?

190
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,368
I only want to exchange information,
that's all.

191
00:22:07,840 --> 00:22:09,444
That must be possible.

192
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:14,762
That must be possible!

193
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,209
Hey, a new cell phone...

194
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,568
Listen to what it says here:

195
00:23:36,080 --> 00:23:39,687
"The number of missing teenagers
has risen recently.

196
00:23:39,880 --> 00:23:41,609
In comparison to recent years,

197
00:23:41,760 --> 00:23:44,525
the number has risen
by a clear margin.

198
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:49,564
Police Inspector Heine claims
it is due to the time of year...

199
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:52,881
It's in the miscellaneous news.

200
00:23:57,760 --> 00:23:58,886
Well, what do you say?

201
00:24:09,280 --> 00:24:11,044
Don't they have school?

202
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:15,650
Do they always meet there?
- I've no idea.

203
00:24:18,040 --> 00:24:20,520
I gave one of them a ride, recently.

204
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:24,922
Strange coincidence, isn't it?

205
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:28,406
Did you see the picture with the rat?

206
00:24:28,680 --> 00:24:29,966
What rat?

207
00:24:32,120 --> 00:24:33,645
A rat with wings.

208
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,811
I don't know, Lothar.

209
00:24:37,360 --> 00:24:39,362
What am I to do about them?

210
00:24:40,960 --> 00:24:43,440
I've no time for other children now.

211
00:24:44,680 --> 00:24:47,889
I think you don't want to know
what's happened.

212
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:51,402
Because I don't watch teenagers
out the window?

213
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:53,370
Why did you call me, then?

214
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:55,847
I thought Martha maybe at yours.

215
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:58,450
I thought she can't stand me.

216
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:01,689
Says who?
- You did, if I'm not mistaken.

217
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,121
That's seven years ago.

218
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:06,086
Exactly. Seven years,
during which I never saw Martha.

219
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,730
Because you just left.

220
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:11,083
Because you wouldn't let me see her.
- Rubbish.

221
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,289
You never took responsibility.

222
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:17,089
You still think
the world turns around you.

223
00:25:18,160 --> 00:25:21,926
Now Martha's vanished and what counts
are your feelings.

224
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:23,361
You're disgusting.

225
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:35,844
Hey!
- What the hell!

226
00:25:36,040 --> 00:25:39,408
What are you doing out at this time?
- Let go of me.

227
00:25:45,480 --> 00:25:46,766
Get in!

228
00:26:02,920 --> 00:26:05,161
What was that?
- A stone, I think.

229
00:26:16,400 --> 00:26:18,641
Where have you been? It's 10:20!

230
00:26:18,840 --> 00:26:20,171
Good evening.

231
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:23,042
Is something wrong?
- Your daughter missed the bus.

232
00:26:23,560 --> 00:26:24,846
I drove her home.

233
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:27,010
What bus?
- Evening.

234
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:29,322
What's wrong with your bike?

235
00:26:29,520 --> 00:26:30,851
It's got a flat.

236
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:34,763
You can't come and go at will.

237
00:26:34,960 --> 00:26:36,371
We had an agreement.

238
00:26:37,920 --> 00:26:39,968
I'm off to bed.
I start early tomorrow.

239
00:26:40,200 --> 00:26:42,123
Say thanks at least.
- Thanks.

240
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,526
Any time.

241
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,365
Won't you come in?

242
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:49,764
I have to go home.
Take good care of her.

243
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,009
What are you doing there?

244
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:12,251
Did I wake you?

245
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,605
No. I need the loo.

246
00:28:16,320 --> 00:28:18,129
What are you doing there?

247
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:20,850
They smashed my window.

248
00:29:15,360 --> 00:29:16,441
Hello.

249
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:19,047
Oh, it's you.
- Is your daughter there?

250
00:29:19,240 --> 00:29:21,083
No. She's still at school.

251
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:22,765
Would you call there?

252
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:25,120
Why should I?

253
00:29:25,520 --> 00:29:27,966
Because I don't think she's there.

254
00:29:29,040 --> 00:29:31,407
I don't know what I make of you.

255
00:29:32,360 --> 00:29:35,489
Do you know your daughter
wanders the country during the day?

256
00:29:37,560 --> 00:29:40,325
I think that's none of your business.

257
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:43,370
No one asked you to keep coming here.
Leave us in peace.

258
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,004
Hey! Stop there!

259
00:35:00,080 --> 00:35:01,411
Hello.
- Hello.

260
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,411
A coffee, please.

261
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:08,971
Was that a break-in?

262
00:35:09,960 --> 00:35:11,485
The second this week.

263
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:13,041
Oh yes?

264
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:16,921
Two girls.

265
00:35:17,120 --> 00:35:20,522
They broke the window,
got in, and off they went.

266
00:35:21,200 --> 00:35:22,645
Did you see the girls?

267
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:25,331
It wasn't my shift.

268
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:27,405
They were 13, 14, I hear.

269
00:35:27,600 --> 00:35:28,965
That's all.

270
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:31,891
What did they steal?

271
00:35:32,560 --> 00:35:35,166
Petty stuff.
Food, crisps, the like.

272
00:35:52,440 --> 00:35:54,169
Oh, crap.

273
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:10,490
What?
